    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <!-- Main Portrait Image -->
            <img src="images/rd-burman-single-color1.jpg" 
                 alt="R.D. Burman Portrait" 
                 class="main-portrait"
                 onerror="this.style.background='linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%)'; this.src='';">
            
            <h1>R.D. BURMAN</h1>
            <div class="subtitle">üéµ Pancham Da - The Musical Genius üé∂</div>
            <div class="dates">27 June 1939 - 4 January 1994</div>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.2rem; color: #555;">
                "The Innovator who Revolutionized Bollywood Music"
            </p>
        </header>

        <nav>
            <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="showTab('video')">üìπ Video</button>
            <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('audio')">üéß Audio</button>
            <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('about')">üìñ About Pancham</button>
            <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('songs')">üéµ Songs Collection</button>
        </nav>

        <!-- VIDEO TAB -->
        <div id="video" class="tab-content active">
            <h2 style="color: #e74c3c; font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">üìπ Video Collection</h2>
            <div id="videoContent" class="content-grid">
                <div class="loading">
                    <div class="spinner"></div>
                    <p>Loading videos from YouTube...</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- AUDIO TAB -->
        <div id="audio" class="tab-content">
            <h2 style="color: #8e44ad; font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">üéß Audio Collection</h2>
            <div id="audioContent" class="content-grid">
                <!-- Audio content will be populated here -->
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ABOUT TAB -->
        <div id="about" class="tab-content">
            <h2 style="color: #8e44ad; font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">üìñ About Pancham Da</h2>
            <div class="biography-section">
                <h2>üéº The Musical Prodigy</h2>
                <p>
                    Rahul Dev Burman, affectionately known as Pancham Da, was born on 27th June 1939 in the vibrant city of Calcutta. 
                    From the very first cry, destiny whispered that this child would change the landscape of Indian music forever. 
                    His nickname "Pancham" originated from a delightful legend - whenever baby Rahul cried, it resonated with the fifth note 
                    (Pa) of the Indian musical scale, as if even his tears were composed in perfect harmony!
                </p>

                <h2>üéπ The Genesis of Genius</h2>
                <p>
                    Born into a royal lineage of music - the son of legendary composer Sachin Dev Burman and lyricist Meera Dev Burman - 
                    young Pancham was destined for greatness. At the tender age of nine, he composed his first song, "Aye Meri Topi Palat Ke Aa," 
                    which his father lovingly incorporated into the film Funtoosh (1956). This was merely the overture to a symphony that would 
                    span over three glorious decades!
                </p>

                <h2>üé∫ The Revolutionary Era</h2>
                <p>
                    Pancham Da didn't just compose music; he orchestrated a revolution! He brought rock 'n' roll, jazz, Western classical, 
                    and electronic sounds into the heart of Bollywood, creating a fusion that was unprecedented and utterly mesmerizing. 
                    His collaboration with legendary singers Asha Bhosle (whom he married in 1980), Kishore Kumar, and Lata Mangeshkar 
                    produced immortal melodies that continue to echo through generations.
                </p>

                <h2>üé™ The Master Craftsman</h2>
                <p>
                    Over his illustrious career, this musical wizard composed scores for an astounding 331 films - 292 in Hindi, 31 in Bengali, 
                    and several in other languages. From the foot-tapping "Mehbooba Mehbooba" (which he sang himself!) to the soul-stirring 
                    "Tere Bina Zindagi Se" and the groovy "Dum Maro Dum," each composition bore the unmistakable stamp of Pancham's genius.
                </p>

                <h2>üé≠ The Human Behind the Legend</h2>
                <p>
                    Beyond the studio lights and recording rooms, Pancham Da was a man of simple pleasures - he loved cooking, watching sports, 
                    and spending time with close friends like Rajesh Khanna and Kishore Kumar. His spontaneity, warmth, and ability to find 
                    music in everyday sounds made him not just a great composer, but a beloved personality.
                </p>

                <h2>üíî The Final Note</h2>
                <p>
                    On 4th January 1994, the maestro left for his heavenly abode following a heart attack, leaving behind a legacy that 
                    would never fade. His last masterpiece, "1942: A Love Story," was released after his passing and earned him a posthumous 
                    Filmfare Award - a bittersweet recognition of his eternal brilliance.
                </p>

                <h2>üåü The Eternal Legacy</h2>
                <p>
                    Even today, decades after his departure, Pancham Da's music continues to inspire, comfort, and energize millions. 
                    His innovative spirit lives on in every remix, every tribute, every new generation of music lovers who discover his 
                    timeless creations. The Filmfare RD Burman Award for New Music Talent, established in 1995, ensures that his name 
                    continues to encourage fresh talent in the industry he revolutionized.
                </p>

                <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #e74c3c; margin-top: 40px; font-weight: bold;">
                    üéµ "Pancham Da didn't just compose music - he composed emotions, memories, and magic!" üé∂
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SONGS TAB -->
        <div id="songs" class="tab-content">
            <h2 style="color: #43e97b; font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">üéµ Songs Collection from Google Drive</h2>
            
            <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffeaa7 0%, #fdcb6e 100%); padding: 30px; border-radius: 15px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <h3 style="color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 15px;">üìÅ Access the Complete Collection</h3>
                <p style="color: #555; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">
                    Access the complete curated collection of R.D. Burman songs organized by films, decades, and genres.
                </p>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1FQNqgfrnppArFoYqkL7eL67-r1GS_ar6" 
                   target="_blank" 
                   style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px 40px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); 
                          color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 50px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: bold; 
                          box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: all 0.3s ease;">
                    üéµ Open Song Collection in Google Drive
                </a>
            </div>

            <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff9a9e 0%, #fad0c4 100%); padding: 25px; border-radius: 15px; margin-top: 30px;">
                <h4 style="color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 15px;">‚ö†Ô∏è Important Note</h4>
                <p style="color: #555; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                    The songs in this collection are for streaming and personal listening only. Please respect copyright laws 
                    and enjoy the music responsibly. All content belongs to their respective copyright holders.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <footer>
            <p>
                "Pancham Da's music transcends time, touching hearts across generations. His melodies are not just songs - 
                they are emotions, memories, and the very soundtrack of our lives."
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: #e74c3c;">
                üéµ Forever in our hearts - R.D. Burman (1939-1994) üé∂
            </p>
        </footer>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Configuration
        const API_BASE_URL = window.location.origin + '/api';

        // List of images in the images folder
        const imageFiles = [
            'rd-burman-single-color1.jpg',
            // Add more image filenames here as they exist in your folder
            // Example: 'rd-burman-2.jpg', 'rd-burman-3.jpg', etc.
        ];

        // Load scrolling header images
        function loadScrollingImages() {
            const scrollingTrack = document.getElementById('scrollingTrack');
            
            // Try to fetch the list of images from the server
            fetch('/api/images/list')
                .then(response => response.json())
                .then(data => {
                    if (data.success && data.images.length > 0) {
                        createScrollingImages(data.images);
                    } else {
                        // Fallback to predefined list
                        createScrollingImages(imageFiles);
                    }
                })
                .catch(error => {
                    console.log('Using default image list');
                    createScrollingImages(imageFiles);
                });
        }

        function createScrollingImages(images) {
            const scrollingTrack = document.getElementById('scrollingTrack');
            
            // Create images twice for seamless loop
            const allImages = [...images, ...images];
            
            allImages.forEach(imageName => {
                const img = document.createElement('img');
                img.src = `images/${imageName}`;
                img.alt = 'R.D. Burman';
                img.className = 'scrolling-image';
                img.onerror = function() {
                    this.style.display = 'none';
                };
                scrollingTrack.appendChild(img);
            });
        }

        // Tab switching function
        function showTab(tabName) {
            const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
            tabs.forEach(tab => tab.classList.remove('active'));
            
            const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
            buttons.forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
            
            document.getElementById(tabName).classList.add('active');
            event.target.classList.add('active');
        }

        // Load video content from backend API
        async function loadVideoContent() {
            const videoContent = document.getElementById('videoContent');
            
            try {
                const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/youtube/search`);
                const data = await response.json();
                
                if (!data.success) {
                    throw new Error(data.error || 'Failed to load videos');
                }
                
                if (!data.videos || data.videos.length === 0) {
                    videoContent.innerHTML = `
                        <div class="error-message">
                            <h3>üìπ No videos found</h3>
                            <p>Please check your YouTube API configuration in the server</p>
                        </div>
                    `;
                    return;
                }
                
                videoContent.innerHTML = data.videos.map(video => `
                    <div class="content-card">
                        <h3>üé¨ ${escapeHtml(video.snippet.title)}</h3>
                        <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: #666; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                            ${escapeHtml(video.snippet.description.substring(0, 150))}${video.snippet.description.length > 150 ? '...' : ''}
                        </p>
                        <iframe 
                            class="video-embed"
                            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/${video.id.videoId}" 
                            frameborder="0" 
                            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" 
                            allowfullscreen
                            loading="lazy">
                        </iframe>
                        <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #888;">
                            Published: ${new Date(video.snippet.publishedAt).toLocaleDateString()}
                        </p>
                    </div>
                `).join('');
                
            } catch (error) {
                console.error('Error loading videos:', error);
                videoContent.innerHTML = `
                    <div class="error-message">
                        <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Error Loading Videos</h3>
                        <p>${escapeHtml(error.message)}</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.95rem;">
                            Please ensure the backend server is running and YouTube API is configured.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                `;
            }
        }

        // Load audio content
        function loadAudioContent() {
            const audioContent = document.getElementById('audioContent');
            
            const famousSongs = [
                { title: 'Mehbooba Mehbooba', film: 'Sholay (1975)', description: 'The iconic song sung by R.D. Burman himself, which became one of the most memorable tracks in Indian cinema.' },
                { title: 'Dum Maro Dum', film: 'Hare Rama Hare Krishna (1971)', description: 'A revolutionary composition that brought Western influences to Bollywood music.' },
                { title: 'Chura Liya Hai Tumne', film: 'Yaadon Ki Baaraat (1973)', description: 'A timeless romantic melody that continues to enchant audiences.' },
                { title: 'Tum Aa Gaye Ho', film: 'Aandhi (1975)', description: 'Beautiful collaboration with Gulzar, showcasing mastery in creating soulful melodies.' },
                { title: 'Tere Bina Zindagi Se', film: 'Aandhi (1975)', description: 'One of the most romantic duets in Hindi cinema history.' },
                { title: 'Piya Tu Ab To Aaja', film: 'Caravan (1971)', description: 'A mesmerizing song with Helen\'s iconic dance performance.' },
                { title: 'Kya Hua Tera Wada', film: 'Hum Kisise Kum Naheen (1977)', description: 'A soulful melody that has touched millions of hearts.' },
                { title: 'Duniya Mein Logon Ko', film: 'Apna Desh (1972)', description: 'A philosophical song with deep lyrics by Anand Bakshi.' }
            ];
            
            audioContent.innerHTML = famousSongs.map(song => `
                <div class="content-card">
                    <h3>üéµ ${song.title}</h3>
                    <p style="color: #8e44ad; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px;">${song.film}</p>
                    <p>${song.description}</p>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 15px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #666;">
                        <strong>üí° Note:</strong> To add streaming audio, integrate with services like Spotify, SoundCloud, or JioSaavn API.
                        Check your Google Drive collection for offline listening.
                    </p>
                </div>
            `).join('');
        }

        // Utility function to escape HTML
        function escapeHtml(text) {
            const div = document.createElement('div');
            div.textContent = text;
            return div.innerHTML;
        }

        // Initialize on page load
        window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            loadScrollingImages();
            loadVideoContent();
            loadAudioContent();
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>